100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On January 8, 1926, the League of Nations convened for discussions on international disarmament, highlighting global efforts to promote peace following the Great War. In the United States, debates continued over Prohibition, with rising tensions among law enforcement and bootleggers. Meanwhile, political unrest persisted in Germany as the Weimar Republic faced economic challenges and calls for reform.
